data.name: cellSizeTrackBar.ToolTip
data.value:
Adjusts the Marching Squares grid cell size.
Increasing the resolution of the mesh will increase the resolution of the extracted mesh, meaning it follows the density field boundary you've set more closely.

data.name: densityThresholdTrackBar.ToolTip
data.value:
Adjusts the threshold which the Marching Algorithm uses to determine the position of the surface to extract.
It aims to draw lines through the field where the density equals the threshold value.
If the extracted lines don't quite encompass the entire area you're after, decrease the density to push the lines further to the edge.
